title: In-Person Ladies Learning Code: Webmaking w/ HTML&CSS
where: Canadian Western Bank Place, 10303 Jasper Ave, 16th Floor, Suite 1650, Edmonton, AB T5J3N6
short_description: Join us for our first in-person event since March 2020! Looking to get your feet wet when it comes to coding? Then this is the workshop for you.
notes_1: Please join us for our first in-person experience since March of 2020!Why learn HTML & CSS? If you are looking to get your feet wet when it comes to coding, then this is the workshop for you. HTML and CSS are the backbone of all websites, and knowledge of them is a necessity if you are interested in things like web development, creating marketing emails, or even blogging! The web without HTML and CSS would be a world without colourful, pretty websites, not to mention the web applications we all use daily. It’s easy to learn, and was designed so that everyone - even non-programmers - can do it. No fancy programs are needed, just a web browser! This workshop is designed to be a hands-on experience. During the session, you’ll learn:Basic techniques and concepts that are translatable to other programming languagesThe building blocks of how HTML and CSS work together to create richer online experiencesHow to create a website with images and a CSS-defined layoutWhat resources are available if you’d like to continue learning at home (and we think you will)Who is this for?Our Ladies Learning Code workshops offer female-identified and male-identified, trans, and non-binary adults hands-on, project-based learning experiences that are designed to give beginners the skills and confidence they need to become digital creators.Prerequisites:None! This workshop is designed for beginners.What's Included:An awesome lead instructor and industry mentors! And for this workshop, the mentors and instructors will be coming from CGI, the Information Technology and business consulting firm!Requirements:You must bring your own laptop for which you have administrative permissions.Please remember to bring your own power cord. A mouse can come in handy too!You may be required to download some free software. After you sign up we will email detailed instructions.We strive to host inclusive, accessible experiences that enable all individuals to engage fully. To request an accommodation or for inquires about accessibility, please contact accessibility@canadalearningcode.ca

title: Open Cockpit Day at the Alberta Aviation Museum
short_description: The Alberta Aviation Museum presents its ever-popular Open Cockpit Day this Fall.
notes_1: Join in on the celebration at the museum’s authentic WWII air hangar and receive a full, unique aviation experience. It’s the one day of the year where people and families of all ages can experience unique and rare historical aircraft up-close and personal in the pilot’s seat!  Take in amiskwaciy Academy’s ê-pimihâyahk (we are all flying together) exhibit and learn about sustainability and the biology of flight at the YEG Honeycomb Resident Beehives. Check out and interact with an exciting line-up of fire trucks, service transports, and military vehicles.  Engage in family programming and exhilarating flight-simulators.  Special guests include members of the Edmonton Flying club, 504 Blatchford Field Air Cadets, Vets Canada and more!Of course, no Open Cockpit is complete without the first-hand experience of sitting in the captain’s seat of a historical aircraft.  This special celebration will see the museum open almost a dozen of its aircraft to the public.  Whether it is to capture the perfect photo for your newsfeeds, or to channel your inner fighter-pilot, there is an aircraft opportunity for everyone!Catch a Glimpse of Some of our Participating Aircraft:•	Noorduyn Norseman IV•	Lockheed TF-104G Starfighter•	Fleet Model 80 Canuck•	Beechcraft Expeditor 3NM (Model 18)•	Canadair CT-133 Silver Star Mk.3AT•	Bell 47G•	Piper PA-18 Super Cub•	de Havilland DH.82C Tiger MothFood trucks, photo booths, and family scavenger hunts with prizes will also be available throughout the day.

title: Electric & Hydrogen Vehicle Expo
where: Edmonton EXPO Centre, 7515 118 Ave NW, Edmonton, AB T5B 0J2
short_description: A free, experiential public event on sustainable transportation.
notes_1: Organized by the City of Edmonton with a financial contribution from Natural Resources Canada, this event is designed to give residents an opportunity to experience zero emission vehicles including battery electric passenger vehicles, hydrogen and electric buses, e-bikes, e-scooters and more. Visitors will have the opportunity to see and test drive zero emission vehicles, learn from industry experts at the Change for Climate Education Stage and visit interactive booths to learn all about zero emission vehicles and their charging infrastructure. Various Edmonton auto dealers will be in attendance with  their latest electric vehicles (EV) models, along with members of the Electric Vehicle Owners Association of Alberta (EVAA) who are excited to show off their cars and talk about their own real-world experience.Don’t miss Ontario's own Plug’n Drive who will be in attendance with their Mobile Electric Vehicle Education Trailer (MEET). MEET is equipped with informational displays, interactive learning tools and some of the latest EV models from leading manufacturers for test drives. Reservations for the MEET test drives are available through EdmontonEVExpo.ca.In Edmonton transportation is responsible for 30% of greenhouse gas emissions and 42% of energy use. Reducing emissions from transportation through the wide adoption of zero emissions vehicles is essential to meet our climate goals as well as improving air quality.

title: The Arctic: Our Last Great Wilderness in IMAX!
where: TELUS World of Science - Edmonton (IMAX Theatre), 11211 142 St NW, Edmonton AB Canada, T5M 4A1
short_description: Embark on a cinematic journey to a world untouched by time in The Arctic: Our Last Great Wilderness in IMAX!
notes_1: Imagine a place that is vast, wild and untouched, where some of the world’s greatest wildlife spectacles unfold. The Arctic National Wildlife refuge, situated in the northeastern corner of Alaska, is the wildest place left in North America. A symbol of wilderness for the world. No one has truly ever seen it. The Arctic: Our Last Great Wilderness will feature the first-ever cinematic account of this little-known land where people can experience a world untouched by time.Take a journey to a place in the far north of Alaska that is vast, wild, and magical – where one of earth’s greatest natural spectacles unfolds. Journey with National Geographic Photographer Florian Schulz on his five-year quest to film one of the longest animal migrations on earth and experience intimate encounters with polar bears, musk oxen, wolves, grizzlies, golden eagles and more.

title: A DANCE DOUBLE BILL OF CONTEMPORARY BALLET FEATURING: Edouard Lock’s ÉCHO and Vanessa Goodman’s TUNING
where: Triffo Theatre, MacEwan University Allard Hall, 11110 104 Ave NW, Edmonton AB T5K
short_description: Triffo Theatre, MacEwan University Allard Hall
notes_1: About ÉCHO ÉCHO, is a new work created and directed by world-renowned choreographer and visionary, Édouard Lock. Interpreted by Principal dancer of Les Grands Ballets Canadiens, Rachele Buriassi. ÉCHO is a work intertwined in reflections and immersed in a cinematic night. “Once again, his imagination is peerless. ÉCHO is so beautiful, so contemporary and so about this beautiful ballet dancer’s DANCING!” This presentation also includes a viewing of Edouard’s film ÉCHO, produced by PHI Studio. About TUNING TUNING is a new duet commissioned by Alexis Fletcher created and directed by Vanessa Goodman featuring dance artists Alexis Fletcher and Ted Littlemore.  This new work focuses on how we tune to one another. In TUNING the performers create a live sonic and physical atmosphere using their voices to amplify the conversations of the body. “When I first saw this dance, I thought I was witnessing a most intimate moment between a couple whose relationship had withstood time. It is beautiful!”

title: Beaver Hills House / Michael Phair Park  Survey
project_name: Beaver Hills House / Michael Phair Park
notes_1: The City is renewing Beaver Hills House Park and Michael Phair Park in downtown Edmonton. In addition to repairing or replacing the existing park infrastructure, the renewal will improve safety,  accessibility and  use of these important open spaces in our downtown. Improvements being considered for the parks include increasing sightlines, grading to improve accessibility, increasing lighting as well as adding new amenities, including a public washroom. Start the survey here

title: 2022 EHS Garden Festival
where: Parkdale-Cromdale Community League (11335 85 Street NW, Edmonton)
cost: Free entry, attendees can choose to spend money at vendors.
short_description: Family-friendly garden festival that unites gardening non-profits, and the public for an afternoon of vendors, learning, food, face-painting, etc.
additional_information: Vendors/Educators(as of time of writing) are: Edmonton Seedy Sunday, Wagner Natural Area Society, Edmonton Native Plant Society, Edmonton African Violet & Gesneriad Society, 102.3 NOW radio Trucksicle. Facepainting will be done by @misskellystudio on Instagram
notes_1: The EHS 2022 Garden Fest is here!On August 21st, 2022 @ 11:00am - 3:00pm, join us at the Parkdale-Cromdale Community League (11335 85st Edmonton) for an afternoon of gardening-related fun and learning for all ages! Activities include vendors, educators, face-painting, photos, food, and more!

title: Level up your run game with the Ultra Night Run!
short_description: The Michelob Ultra Night Run is a one-of-a-kind, in-person and virtual 5K/10K Race https://www.ultranightrun.ca/
notes_1: Join Michelob Ultra as we encourage Canadians to level-up their run game by participating in the Michelob Ultra Night Run, returning for its 5th year! This year’s 5K / 10K run will feature a nighttime course packed with lights, sounds and interactive elements, ending in a after-party complete with beer garden. Can’t attend the in-person race? No problem! Make the Michelob Ultra Night Run your own and run it virtually from your own neighbourhood or even at home on your treadmill from September 23-September 25! Registration comes with a race kit that includes everything you need to stay bright as you race against the night with friends, family, your community of runners or solo. Tickets range from $40.00 - $65.00, register at https://bit.ly/3oRISyu  Consider joining the runners of the Michelob Ultra Night Run at the official city afterparty for a cold one, or even enjoy a Michelob Utra at home, because ‘It’s Only Worth It If You Enjoy It’.       Additional Details: Ages 19+| Registration fees range from $40.00 CAD - $65.00 CAD

title: BGN-Overlander/Homesteader pop up event
where: Homesteader Community League and Park, 575 Hermitage Road NW, Edmonton, AB
notes_1: Overlanders and Homesteader have been chosen for neighbourhood renewal. Planning begins now for construction starting in spring 2025, with anticipated completion by the end of 2027.Let's get to know each other! Join us at Community League Day to meet the project team and share what your neighbourhood means to you.

title: The Eleven O'clock Number
where: The Grindstone Comedy Theatre, 10019 81 Ave NW, Edmonton, AB T6E 1W7
short_description: The Grindstone's award winning improvised musical comedy, The Eleven O'clock Number is performing at the Fringe Festival!
notes_1: The Eleven O'clock Number is Grindstone's award winning improvised musical comedy! Based on suggestions from the audience the cast improvises a brand new musical comedy on the spot. Complete with twisting plots and showstopping numbers, Laughs are guaranteed. You have to see it to believe it!Performers:Byron Martin, Abby Lynn Vandenberghe, Dallas Friesen, Malachi Wilkins, Mhairi Berg,  Evan Dowling, Sarah Dowling, Chris Borger, Katie Hudson, Neil Kuefler, and Mark Vetsch. Accompanied by musicians, (who are also improvising the entire time!) Simon Abbott and Curtis den Otter.

title: (Thunder)CATS
where: Trinity Lutheran Church, 10014 81 Ave NW, Edmonton, AB T6E 1W8
where_to_purchase_tickets: Visit the Fringe website for tickets! https://tickets.fringetheatre.ca/event/601:4321/
short_description: From the writers of Jason Kenney's Hot Boy Summer, (Thunder)CATS is an original musical satire performing at the Fringe Festival.
additional_information: Show dates:12 AUG 2022, FRI 11pm – 12am13 AUG 2022, SAT 9:15 – 10:15pm14 AUG 2022, SUN 9:15 – 10:15pm15 AUG 2022, MON 9:15 – 10:15pm16 AUG 2022, TUE 11pm – 12am18 AUG 2022, THU 11pm – 12am20 AUG 2022, SAT 2:15 – 3:15pm21 AUG 2022, SUN 12 – 1pm
notes_1: From the writers of Jason Kenney's Hot Boy Summer, (Thunder)CATS is an original musical satire of Broadways "most loved" feline musical, with less plot, tighter leotards and one throbbing mystical sword!The plot? The Thunderians, fleeing the destruction of their home planet, have landed on planet Thundera and await the ghost of their fallen leader Jaga The Wise to find out which ThunderCAT character will return to the ThunderCAT Lair. Through obscene hip thrusting and way too much dancing, they learn what it really means to be a Thunder CAT. With a stacked cast of Edmonton’s professional actors, singers and dancers, (Thunder)CATS is a hit musical that will slap you across the face with comedy. - You can’t unsee this show.Performers:Donovan Workun, Stephanie Wolfe, Sarah Dowling, Owen Bishop, David Son, Paul-Ford Manguelle, Brennan Campbell, and Kristin Unruh. Accompanied by musicians Simon Abbott, Jesse Crowley, and Alex Downey.

title: PLANET B "Stories From Beyond The Stars"
where: The Lumos Dental Stage, 9562 82 Ave NW, Edmonton, AB T6C 1B9
short_description: Grindstone Theatre School’s Long-Form Improv Conservatory Presents: PLANET B "Stories From Beyond The Stars"
notes_1: Grindstone Theatre School’s Long-Form Improv Conservatory Presents:PLANET B"Stories From Beyond The Stars"In a universe not too distant from ours; in a time not too distant from now, lives a people, not too distant from ourselves! Welcome to Planet B! Grindstone's Improv Conservatory brings you "Stories from Beyond the Stars", a sci-fi exploration of comedies and tragedies that are out of this world!Performers:Christopher Corbett, Ed Picard, Heather Nicholson, Julie Sucie, Tylor Ell, Ben Rollans, Marie Carrillos Avalos, Lea DuCoeur, Monica Gate Directed by: Lee Boyes  Show Times: August 12 - 11:00PM / August 13 - 7:30PM / August 14 - 4:00PM / August 15 - 7:30PMAugust 17 - 9:15PM / August 19 - 11:00PM / August 20 - 2:15PM / August 21 - 5:15PM Tickets: $13 + $3 Fringe Processing FeeTickets available here: https://tickets.fringetheatre.ca/event/601:4297/

title: Come From Away
where_to_purchase_tickets: Tickets can be purchased through ticketmaster.ca
short_description: Award winning musical Come From Away returns to Edmonton.
notes_1: The true story of the small town that welcomed the world.Broadway’s COME FROM AWAY has won Best Musical all across North America!The New York Times Critics’ Pick takes you into the heart of the remarkable true story of 7,000 stranded passengers and the small town in Newfoundland that welcomed them. Cultures clashed and nerves ran high, but uneasiness turned into trust, music soared into the night, and gratitude grew into enduring friendships.Don’t miss this breathtaking new musical written by Tony nominees Irene Sankoff and David Hein, and helmed by this year’s Tony Award-winning Best Director, Christopher Ashley. Newsweek cheers, “It takes you to a place you never want to leave!”On 9/11, the world stopped. On 9/12, their stories moved us all.

title: Jubefest: The Heebee-Jeebees
where: Northern Alberta Jubilee Auditorium, 11455 87 Ave NW, Edmonton, AB T6G 2T2, Canada
short_description: Northern Alberta Jubilee Auditorium
notes_1: Jubefest is back for another summer! The Heebee-jeebees™ are an internationally acclaimed, award-winning, comic a cappella group born and raised in Calgary. Having celebrated over 25 years together, they have released 8 CDs and have won 3 international CARA awards – the Grammys of a cappella. The Heebee-jeebees have sung thousands of live performances and have appeared on local, national and international radio and television. The group has a reputation for being hilarious, entertaining and extremely talented. You can find their studio recordings on iTunes & Spotify. Follow them on Twitter and Facebook or at heebee-jeebees.com They are the most FUN you've ever heard! Join us as we enjoy the talents of The Heebee-Jeebees on our outdoor patio!

title: The Fourth R: reduce, reuse, recycle, REVOLUTIONIZE
short_description: Downtown Edmonton
notes_1: We cannot wait to celebrate the Earth together and unite in our fight for climate justice with our theatrical, multi media dance show, THE FOURTH R! We all know the situation: the planet, the people and the animals are in a really tough spot. Animals and resources are becoming extinct, the CO2 levels are rising and the Arctic is melting. But there is hope - and it’s US!We are a group from Toronto travelling to Edmonton to take part in the Edmonton Fringe Festival. Come fight for the planet with us at the Gateway Theatre!Run time: 50 minutes

title: Wild Moo's Chase -  A New Musical
where: La Cit? Francophone Theatre - 8627 91 Street Edmonton, Alberta T6C3N1
where_to_purchase_tickets: Tickets can be purchased through the Edmonton Fringe Festival website: https://tickets.fringetheatre.ca/event/601:4338/by phone at 780-409-1910or in person at the Fringe Theatre Arts Barns Box Office (10330 84 Avenue).
short_description: Wild Moo’s Chase: A NEW Edmonton made musical premiering at the Edmonton Fringe Festival!
notes_1: From the creators of Murder Mime: The Musical, The Grave Digger, & The Big Bright comes a brand new musical!Wild Moo’s Chase is premiering this summer at the Edmonton Fringe Festival from Friday, August 12th to Sunday, August 21st 2022 at the La Cité Francophone Theatre!Wild Moo’s Chase tells the story of Filet and her sister, Brisket, who live in the whimsical, diluted, pun-filled town called Meatland. In a constant battle between curiosity and managing her mental health, Filet finds herself unable to open the literal door and get answers. Once she finds a poster that conflicts with everything she was taught, she decides to face her disorder and learn the truth.Venue: La Cité Francophone Theatre (8627 91 Street Edmonton)Show Dates & Times:Fri Aug. 12th - 12:30pmSat Aug. 13th - 7:30pmSun Aug. 14th - 4:15pmMon Aug. 15th - 3:15pmTue Aug. 16th - 7:30pmThu Aug. 18th - 9:15pmFri Aug. 19th - 5:30pmSat Aug. 20th - 4:00pmSun Aug. 21st - 12:30pmApproximate runtime: 90 minutesTickets are $13 and can be purchased through the Edmonton Fringe Festival website: https://tickets.fringetheatre.ca/event/601:4338/, by phone at 780-409-1910or in person at the Fringe Theatre Arts Barns Box Office (10330 84 Avenue). Visit the Edmonton Fringe Festival website for more information on Wild Moo’s Chase: https://tickets.fringetheatre.ca/event/601:4338/

title: jubefest: Mocking Shadows
where: Northern Alberta Jubilee Auditorium, 11455 87 Ave NW, Edmonton, AB T6G 2T2, Canada
short_description: Northern Alberta Jubilee Auditorium
notes_1: Jubefest is back for another summer! Mocking Shadows have been entertaining crowds across Canada for over 10 years, burnin' down the house with their own brand of soul, reggae, blues, and R&B. Classic old-school Motown grooves get a contemporary treatment making this band a winner for all ages: from teens to boomers. The music, showmanship, and creativity have only gotten better with time, and their strong new sound and energetic show has earned the Mocking Shadows a place on the new Canadian Music scene with a current line up boasting talent from both Edmonton & Calgary. Join us as we enjoy the talents of Alberta-based band Mocking Shadows on our outdoor patio.

title: BEAMS @ Idylwylde
cost: Free to Idylwylde community, $7 BEAMS members, $15 general
short_description: Family-friendly electronic music exhibition and show.
notes_1: A live concert and a free family-friendly interactive electronic gallery comprise the itinerary of same-day events presented by the Idlylwylde Community League and the Boreal Electroacoustic Music Society. Both are slated to take place at the Idylwylde Community Hall (8631-81 Street) Saturday August 13. The exhibition runs from 2 p.m. to 8 p.m., when the live show starts.On tap to play the concert are multi-instrumentalist Trevor DePagie, sequencer specialist Stephen Sereda, sound artist Wayne DeFehr, teen electronic dance music performer Noah Benavides, clarinet player and composer Don Ross, and DJ das Weichei.Concert admission is free to Idylwylde Community League members, $7 for BEAMS members, and $15 for the public. For further information, contact BEAMS at info@beams.ca.

title: Jubefest: Maria Dunn
where: Northern Alberta Jubilee Auditorium -, 11455 87 Ave NW, Edmonton, AB T6G 2T2
short_description: 11455 87 Ave NW, Edmonton, AB T6G 2T2
notes_1: Jubefest is back for another summer! 2022 Juno-winning songwriter, Maria Dunn celebrates stories of resilience and grace through songs of family, community, humanity and the love that fires our actions to make the world a better place. Edmonton-based, Maria tours internationally. Maria Dunn’s four-piece ensemble for this concert will include Joyful Banner Blazing producer Shannon Johnson (violin) and Jeremiah McDade (saxophone, whistle, guitar) and Solon McDade (upright bass), all members of Juno Award-winning band The McDades. Together they perform Maria’s thought-provoking, hope-mongering songs in rich and varied arrangements with compelling vocals and superb musicianship. Join us on our outdoor patio as we enjoy the talents of Maria Dunn!

title: HOW I MET MY MOTHER
where: Sue Paterson Theatre at Campus Saint Jean - 8406 91st Street
short_description: An irresponsible bachelor answers the call to care for his ailing mother, while reckoning with his troubled past.
notes_1: n irresponsible bachelor answers the call to care for his ailing mother, while reckoning with his troubled past. But will his new-found skills be enough? A true story of love, family and the power of redemption.25 year Fringe veteran Jon Paterson (Outstanding Solo Show – London, Outstanding Male Performance – Orlando) premieres his first solo-written show on the Canadian Fringe Festival circuit.

title: Edmonton Stamp Club 2022 Summer Auction
short_description: Edmonton Stamp Club Auction
notes_1: Just $2.00 (a toonie) will provide you with a “one day” “Edmonton Stamp Club Membership to attend the ESC summer auction.  It will also buy you a “bidding” card, to participate in the auctioning of over 200 “stamp and cover” related lots. This includes Canada, Worldwide and Topical collections. ​An added feature to this year’s ESC Summer Auction is a “silent auction”, which will begin at 6:30pm. Place your bids on paper, and the highest bidder wins!​Come out and participate in an evening of fun and fellowship with ESC Directors & Members, and enjoy an assortment of sandwiches, snacks and coffee provided by Ella Euro Catering.​Additionally, during Auction hours, (5 pm - 8:30 pm), NEW Edmonton Stamp Club Single or Family Annual Memberships will be available at HALF PRICE!  Payment will be by cheque or cash, and donations are always appreciated. Proceeds of the Summer Auction will go to the ESC in promoting the benefits of stamp collecting “FUN for the FAMILY”, with the balance to the consigners.  During this year's Summer Auction, The Edmonton Stamp Club is partnering with, and proudly supports Edmonton's Food Bank, to help those less fortunate in our community. Please bring a non-perishable food donation during evening events (5:00 pm - 8:30 pm).  A “drop off point” for donations has been established at the front entrance of the Central Lions Recreation Centre.We hope to see you there!

title: Londonderry's 4th Annual Classic Car Show n' Shine
short_description: A great day of classic cars and socializing!
notes_1: Start your engines! We are hosting our 4th Annual Classic Car Show n' Shine, in partnership with Car Buffs of Edmonton. Enjoy a day out in the sunshine and check out beautiful classics! The show will start at 11:00am and wrap up at 3:30pm. Registration is FREE and begins at 10am! There will be prizes every half hour, 50/50 draw and a People's Choice Award for a $500 Londonderry Gift Card! The show will take place at Londonderry's South Parking Lot. Mark your calendars and shine those tires!

title: Edmonton’s Aviation History: More Than a Century of Adventure (An Alberta Aviation Museum Online Lecture Series)
cost: Free for Museum Members, $7.50 for non-members
short_description: Join Alberta Aviation Museum curator Ryan Lee on a twelve-chapter journey through the history of aviation, from a uniquely Edmonton perspective.
notes_1: This Month’s Online Lecture:Lecture 8 – Edmontonians at home in WWIIAugust 31, 2022With the advent of the war in Europe, a surge of activity transforms Edmonton’s airport virtually overnight. With the Edmonton Flying Club and Canadian Airways supporting the British Commonwealth Air Training Plan at No. 16 Elementary Flying Training School and No. 2 Air Observer School, to the arrival of the United States’ Air Transport Command ferrying lend-lease aircraft to the Soviet Union, and the massive maintenance depot at Aircraft Repair Ltd, Edmonton’s skies are constantly busy.Registrations end at 4:00pm on the day of the lecture.

title: Links Fore Literacy Golf Tournament
short_description: The Links at Spruce Grove, 100 Links Rd, Spruce Grove, AB T7X 3B4
notes_1: The Centre for Family Literacy is a nonprofit in Edmonton that offers free literacy programs, training, and resources for families and adults. Our annual Links Fore Literacy Golf Tournament supports the Centre's Classroom on Wheels (C.O.W.) Bus Program — a community initiative offering drop-ins for children and parents, where free books can be borrowed. The event will include free breakfast, a lunch banquet, awards ceremony, and much more!

title: Alberta Aviation Museum Sensory Nights
cost: $15/adults, $12/students/seniors, $10.50/youth 13-17, and $9.50/children 6-12. Children 5 and under are free.
short_description: On the 3rd Thursday of every month, families, individuals and members of the neurodiverse community can experience the wonders of historic Hangar 14.
notes_1: Experience a worry-free, after-hours experience as the museum creates a calming environment to celebrate Edmonton’s rich aviation history.  Over 30 historical aircraft grace the halls as the lights are dimmed and the audio displays are turned town to provide silent, thoughtful, engaging experiences for all ages.

title: Green Your Ravine!
where_to_purchase_tickets: To confirm your attendance please email rootfortrees@edmonton.ca
short_description: Join Root for Trees Saturday August 13th, for community tree planting & educational activities at Sifton Dog Off Leash Park!
notes_1: In a joint effort, TD Bank, and the Arbor Day Foundation are collaborating with the City of Edmonton's Root for Trees program to plant native species of trees and shrubs in Edmonton’s Sifton Dog Off Leash Ravine Park. Root for Trees will be hosting a community tree planting event on Saturday August 13th, 2022 from 10 a.m. - 2 p.m. All Edmontonians are welcome to attend this free event.Activities will include public tree planting, a food truck, educational activities and/or exhibitors, as well as community engagement to aid the appreciation of nature along the green space in Sifton Dog Off Leash Ravine Park. Please wear closed toed shoes and dress for the weather!

Programming is designed for ages 4-12, but nature lovers of all ages are welcome.

title: Alcohol in Designated Picnic Areas Survey
project_name: Alcohol Consumption in Designated Picnic Sites
notes_1:
This survey will ask you for your feedback and opinions about alcohol consumption in city parks.
  • The results of this survey along with public engagement, research, enforcement, financial, and operational data will be used to evaluate the pilot program.
  • You can obtain additional information on the pilot program by visiting the City of Edmonton’s website or by calling 311.

title: Shifting Articulations of Asian-ness in Contemporary Canad
short_description: This exhibition features works from 12 artists that demonstrate the persistence and resilience of Asian experiences.
notes_1: Come explore a recently opened online exhibit: Shifting Articulations of Asian-ness in Contemporary CanadaProduced by independent curator Yang Lim, this exhibition features works from 12 artists that demonstrate the persistence and resilience of Asian experiences.Highlighting diverse perspectives within Canada’s Asian communities, this exhibition broadens the conversation around “Asian-ness” and complicates what it means to be part of Canada’s Asian diaspora today. It features twelve artists of Asian heritage whose works engage with intersecting narratives, communities, and discursive contexts that navigate the complexities of “Asian-ness” and Asian identities.Some of these artists explore how specific objects and places can become infused with culturally specific meanings that bridge different generations and contribute to a sense of shared heritage. Other artists reveal how intangible things such as language, music, and memories can embody a collective experience or legacy, providing an anchor for redefining or reimagining what it means to belong to a specific community. Some works reshape understandings of “Asian-ness” that have become associated with specific objects and places. The creation of the works themselves becomes a means to make “Asian-ness” visible and to expose its absence in contexts that have rendered “Asian-ness” invisible.This exhibition’s works demonstrate the persistence and resilience of Asian experiences that should be considered, in their own right, as meaningful and valuable for the people who belong to those communities.Enjoy this online multimedia exhibit from June 25th to August 7th!This exhibition is funded with support from the Edmonton Arts Council and the City of Edmonton.Get social with us!Instagram: @artistryprojectsTwitter: @artisteprojectsFacebook: @intersectionsinart

title: 13th annual Pride of the Northside Tournament
short_description: The Pride of the Northside: Block Party, Community event, Basketball tournament
notes_1: The Pride of the Northside 4 on 4 Streetball tournament is a 2 day full weekend event in the heart of North Edmonton Streetball culture: Londonderry Outdoor courts. The Tournament was created to uplift the community and to showcase the vibrant streetball and hip hop culture in Northeast Edmonton. Community Barbecue, musical performances, dance competitions, Live DJ, on-site Physiotherapy, 3 point and Slam and Competitions; we do it all in the name of celebrating sport in the city of Edmonton. Every 3rd week of August since August 2009 this tournament has served as a fundraiser, block party, and basketball showcase in the city of Edmonton. This community event is more than a tournament and the participants are a part of a long tradition of community outreach.

title: Music is Medicine 2022
where: Across from the University of Alberta Hospital's 112 St Entrance (at the picnic tables)
short_description: Music is Medicine music series is back for another summer!
notes_1: The Friends of University Hospital's annual Music is Medicine music series is back for another summer! We’re thrilled that so many local musicians will be coming by the University of Alberta Hospital and performing for the community! This year’s line-up includes some of our past performers such as The Aquarius Duo (performed in 2021), Lindon Carter (performed in 2021), Karimah (performned in 2019), and Kimberley MacGregor (performed in 2021). Joining our Music is Medicine family are VISSIA, Josh Sahunta, and Matthew and The Keys! We’re incredibly excited to see so many amazing performers! Performers and dates are listed below. Performances will be held at the picnic tables across from the University of Alberta Hospital’s 112 St Entrance. All performances are subject to rescheduling if the weather chooses not to cooperate, though we will try to reschedule if it happens. Welcome to summer!

title: Kaleido Family Arts Festival: Hearts in Living Colour Returns to Alberta Avenue and they need YOU!
short_description: Parkdale Cromdale Community League
notes_1: Arts on the Ave is pleased to present Kaleido Family Arts Festival 2022: Hearts in Living Colour, September 16 - 18, 2022. Kaleido is coming back to the Ave, bringing light, joy and filling hearts with music, art, and acts that are a wonder to behold, and (as always) free to the community!Kaleido is currently seeking volunteers to help make the festival magic happen. Share your talents or hone your skills - positions are available for a wide range of abilities and interests. Work with marvellous people on fun teams, or strengthen bonds with friends and family by signing up together! Receive a colourful festival t-shirt and other fabulous perks.Kaleido is hosting volunteer events, June 23, July 13 and August 24, at the Parkdale Cromdale Community League. Each event is an opportunity to learn more about the festival and volunteer positions. The evenings include a fun theme, delicious meal, entertainment and a sneak peek at the festival. Please note, that individuals should RSVP for one event only. For more information about the 2022 Kaleido Family Arts Festival, visit kaleidofest.ca.

title: District Planning Project Survey
notes_1: The District Planning project is establishing a new type of geographic plan for each of the 15 districts identified in The City Plan. Under the umbrella of an overall District General Policy, each individual district plan will guide how districts change—where infill will occur, where parks are needed, where active transportation routes need improving—over time as envisioned in The City Plan. The District General Policy (DGP) contains citywide policy direction applicable to places and features found in all districts. The City is gathering public and stakeholder input on the District General Policy content.Start the survey here

title: Daniel O'DOnnell
short_description: Daniel O'Donnel is coming to the River Cree Resort & Casino on September 25th 2022
notes_1: Irish singer and entertainer, Daniel O’Donnell is performing at River Cree Resort & Casino in Edmonton on September 25th 2022.The Donegal based singer, who is one of the most prolific and successful recording artists in the UK charts, is the only artist in the world to score a hit in the UK album charts every year since 1988, an unprecedented and unbroken 34-year span, and in doing so, he has outshone everyone from Michael Jackson and Madonna, to U2 and the Rolling Stones.A multifaceted entertainer, O’Donnell has also starred in several TV programs including PBS’ The Daniel O’Donnell Show, Daniel and Majella's B&B Road Trip, Room to Improve, Opry Le Daniel and much more.After more than 40 years in the spotlight, Daniel has been awarded many accolades including an induction into Ireland’s Music Hall of Fame and received multiple Entertainer of the Year/Person of the Year Awards in Ireland and the UK.He released his latest album ‘Daniel O’Donnell 60’ in 2021.

title: The Filipino in Me - Insights into Living Heritage
short_description: An online exhibit of multimedia works on Philippine living heritage themes in Canada. In celebration of Philippine Heritage Month.
notes_1: The Filipino in Me - Insights into Living Heritage is an online exhibit of multimedia works on Philippine living heritage themes in Canada.This event aims to explore the unique qualities and build an inventory of Philippine living heritage in Canada. It aims to encourage art creation, and an appreciation on how art can engage the community and the exploration of heritage. This is a wonderful opportunity to further artistic practice, promote Philippine culture , and showcase original works to the public.

notes_1: Ready for a laugh? Don’t miss the exclusive one-night-only comedy show featuring cult comedy icons Kevin Smith and Jason Mewes as their legendary characters, “Jay” and “Silent Bob”, together on stage. From Quick Stop to Edmonton, this is your chance to clock in for an evening of jokes and stories you won’t hear anywhere else – too good to miss! title: Edmonton Comics & Entertainment Expo
where: Edmonton Expo Centre, 7515 118 Ave NW, Edmonton, AB T5B 0J2
cost: Ticket prices vary, starting at $21 per day for early bird pricing (available until May 31), $32 per day at the door. 3-Day Passes, Family Passes and Premium Packages are also available.
short_description: Edmonton Comics & Entertainment Expo is a 3-day celebration of all things pop culture.
notes_1: Edmonton Comics & Entertainment Expo is a 3-day celebration of all things pop culture. After three years apart, come together with your fellow fans to geek out over comics, sci-fi, anime, gaming, cosplay and more. Whatever you’re a fan of, you’ll find it at Edmonton Expo!  There’s so much to do at the show — for all ages! Shop hundreds of artists, artisans, and specialty vendors for that impossible-to-find treasure. Snap selfies with favourite costumed characters on the show floor, and experience the culture of Edmonton’s incredible, creative fan community. Meet the creators building your favourite worlds and learn from the experts in ‘how to' workshops.  Edmonton Expo brings fandom’s biggest stars face-to-face with fans! Get an autograph or a photo with your favourite celebrity guest then get the inside scoop during epic on-stage panels. This year, you can meet Ming-Na Wen (The Book of Boba Fett), Matthew Lewis (Harry Potter), Michael Rooker (Guardians of the Galaxy), Tom Welling (Smallvillle), Lana Parrilla (Once Upon a Time), Lou Ferrigno (The Incredible Hulk), Ryan Hurst (Sons of Anarchy), Kevin Smith and Jason Mewes (Jay and Silent Bob)! Not to mention epic creators, cosplayers, gaming and voice guests, and more. You can check out the full guest list at edmontonexpo.com.  Come in cosplay, or come as you are — Edmonton Comics & Entertainment Expo is for everyone! For more information and tickets, visit edmontonexpo.com.

title: K-Days
where: Edmonton EXPO Centre & Exhibition Lands, 7515 118 Ave NW, Edmonton, Alberta , T5B 0J2
cost: In advance prices: Adult $15, Youth & Senior $10, Children 6 & Under free, 10 Day Pass $29.99, Family Pack $40 (2 adults, 2 youth), Ride All Day $48, Fast Pass $20
where_to_purchase_tickets: You can purchase your tickets in advance at K-Days.com or visit one of our partner location Costco, Save On Foods and Circle K. Tickets will also be available on site.
short_description: Edmonton's annual summer fair where you will experience 10 days of pure joy and excitement!
notes_1: Experience The Wonder Of The Midway At K-DaysEdmonton’s extravaganza of rides, games, music, food and adventure. The rides and games alone will leave you breathless and wanting more. Watch as fireworks light up the night sky and cheer for the band onstage. Savour the tangy smokiness of a perfectly barbecued rib, taste the warm sugary bliss of freshly fried donuts and bite into the gooey crispness of a candy apple.Take the kids to Kids Zone where they can see some of North America’s top entertainers for children. Discover the Indigenous Hall with authentic food, shopping and entertainment. Head to the Mainstage for a killer lineup of concerts. Then there's  the Agriculture Hall, or the Maker Faire... and that's just the beginning. There’s something for everyone at Edmonton’s incredible K-Days!

title: Disco In The Park
where: Louise McKinney Park, 9999 Grierson Hill NW, Edmonton, AB T5H 2A4
short_description: Edmonton's summertime House and Disco music festival; A weekend of all day dancing in a beautiful park in the centre of the city.
additional_information: IMPORTANT EVENT INFO-2PM until 10PM on both Saturday July 30 & Sunday July 31.Noon to 6PM children are free and welcome with adult supervision only.6PM to 10PM is 18+ only.Tickets: Tickets can be purchased online for the entirety of the festival or at the door. Bring your ticket on your phone or printed to scan. Wristbands will be provided at the front gate and must be maintained for the two day event. Re-entry is welcome at anytime throughout the festival. If your wrist band breaks or is showing signs that it will break please bring it to the front door immediately for a replacement. Wristbands that show any tampering will not be allowed re-entryParking: Some parking is available at Louise McKinney park, but spaces are limited! Some additional parking is available towards downtown at the top of Grierson Hill. Do not drink and drive.Food & Drink: Alcoholic and non-alcoholic beverages are available throughout the weekend. Food will be available throughout the weekend. ATM's are on site, and debit payment will be available. Sealed water, juice and pop are welcome as well as small sealed snacks and fruit.We are providing free water at our refill station for use throughout the weekend (bring an empty bottle to use at our water refill station if you'd like to reduce waste).Security and Safety: Bag checks will happen at the door, as well as random pat downs. If you feel sick or unsafe in any way, please seek out help from our first aid trained Security Staff (Benaiah Guarding), Management or Food and Beverage Service team.Covid-19 Screening  Please do not come on the day of the event if you are feeling any symptoms of illness. Masks are not required but they are welcome. Social distancing is encouraged as possible, but not required, but please be aware of and respect the personal boundaries of others around you. Sanitizer will be available at the entrance and food and beverage stations.Art: Min Bid will be doing live art on site, check it out! + ask the VJ how you can be a part of the live visuals on screen!Smoking: There will be a designated smoking area outside the gated event.Washrooms: Public washrooms are located in the facilities south of the event site as well as a single WC beside the food tent.Kids: Kids are free and welcome before 5PM (with adult supervision!), but if you are bringing children, please be prepared to take them home at 5PM, as after 5PM minors are prohibited. Please ensure no minors remain on site at that time.Supply list: We encourage you to bring - hats, sunglasses, sun screen, beach blankets, umbrellas, sealed water and small sealed snacks.Please do not bring: Outside alcohol, Outside meals, Dogs or other Animals, WeaponsDress up if you want! Be yourself and have fun!
notes_1: SWEAT and The Grindstone present The 2nd Annual Disco In The Park Festival!Fully licensed, food available, surrounded by trees, lots of room to spread out, and unreal DJ sets and live performances all day from local talents and headlining guests from around the world, plus 3 nights of wild late night club events. Spend your long weekend with us for unforgettable vibes.FEATURING: JELLYBEAN BENITEZ (STUDIO 54, NYC)ANGELO FERRERI (MOODFUNK, ITALY)KATHY BROWN & TAZ (UK)HOTMOOD (DISCOWEEY, MEXICO) THE BRASSTACTICS (Live) | COZMIC CAT (Toronto) | CYCLIST (Toronto) | FUNK HUNK (Denver) | DUNMORE PARK (Toronto) Wijit (Sunshine After Dark) | Maurice | Junior Brown | Work Party & Wax Theory | Oh-Me & Femme Funk | Back To Life DJs | Joses | St. Croix | Mae | ANZU | Ben Colmen | Dusty Grooves | Will Hempfree | YuriFriday July 29 Pre-Party featuring HATIRAS (Spacedisco Records, Toronto) 2 Nightly After Parties (The Grindstone, 9910 and The Bower)After party events and daily lineup TBA.

title: Monster Jam - 30th Anniversary
where: Commonwealth Stadium -- 11000 Stadium Rd. Edmonton, AB T5H 4E2
where_to_purchase_tickets: Tickets are affordably priced for the whole family!Tickets and Pit Passes are now available for purchase online at Ticketmaster.ca *Ticket prices subject to change – additional venue/ticketing fees may apply
short_description: Monster Jam is roaring back into Edmonton with word-class drivers: Grave Digger®, El Toro Loco®, Soldier Fortune™, Megalodon® and more live in action!
additional_information: The most action-packed motorsports experience for families in the world today returns to Edmonton after a five-year hiatus with the first-ever stadium competition event revving through the home of the Edmonton Elks for its debut appearance at Commonwealth Stadium on July 30, 2022.  Celebrating its 30th anniversary this year, Monster Jam features world-class athletes locked in intense competitions of speed and skill.  The popular Monster Jam Pit Party fan experience is scheduled for Saturday, where fans can see the massive trucks up close, meet their favorite drivers and crews, take pictures and enjoy other family-friendly fun.  This unique experience is the only place that allows people to get up close access to the Monster Jam teams and get an insider’s look at how these trucks are built to stand up to the competition.  Pit Passes are available for $20 for this VIP experience.Edmonton motorsports fans will witness heated rivalries, high-flying stunts and fierce head-to-head battles for the Event Championship.  Engineered to perfection, the 12,000-pound Monster Jam trucks push all limits going head-to-head for points in Freestyle, Skills, Donuts and Racing competitions.    Monster Jam drivers are trained, world-class male and female athletes who have mastered not only the physical strength and mental stamina needed to compete, but the vital dexterity to control 12,000-pound machines capable of doing backflips, vertical two-wheel skills and racing at speeds up to 70 miles-per-hour to produce jaw-dropping, live motorsports action seen around the world.  The Edmonton event features eight skilled athletes fighting for the championship while putting on a spectacle, constantly innovating and always entertaining.  Tyler Menninga gets behind the wheel of the legendary black and green wrecking machine Grave Digger®, which is celebrating its 40th anniversary this year.  Elvis Lainez gets back behind the wheel of El Toro Loco®, Bernard Lyght makes his debut in Megalodon® and military veteran Kayla Blood in Soldier Fortune™ look to lock in the event championship. Rounding out the line-up is Travis Mowery piloting Rockwell R.E.D. against Dalton Widner in Jurassic Attack plus two remaining trucks/drivers to be announced soon.

title: Filipino Food Fiesta - Search For Best Filipino Foods 2022
where_to_purchase_tickets: Tickets will be sold at the Pavilion 2, Goldbar Park, August 6 - 7, 2022.
short_description: Filipino Food Festival - Search for Best Filipino Foods, All participants are licensed and have food safety certificate.
additional_information: This is a project of The Association of Friendly Filipino-Canadians of Edmonton (TAFFCE) to raise funds for our outreach programs for homeless, children, and seniors. TAFFCE is a registered not for profit association with the Government of Alberta. This Filipino Food Fiesta - Search for Best Filipino Foods 2022 aimed to promote Filipino restaurants, caterers, and individuals who has license on food handling and has business permits. Foods will be prepared using their licensed kitchen. Foods will be sold to visitors using a coupon provided by TAFFCE.
notes_1: This will be holding a competition for licensed Filipino restaurants, caterers, and individuals. Our Association is aiming to promote all Filipino restaurants in Edmonton. They will be judge according to their sales and judges evaluation.

notes_1: This will be holding a competition for licensed Filipino restaurants, caterers, and individuals. Our Association is aiming to promote all Filipino restaurants in Edmonton. They will be judge according to their sales and judges evaluation.

title: Drive: Reimagine the Ride
short_description: Let your imagination run wild in our new feature exhibition, DRIVE: Reimagining the Ride
notes_1: Vehicles help us work, play, and move. Some of them help us dream, and some might be made of dreams. Let your imagination run wild in our new feature exhibition, DRIVE: Reimagining the Ride, opening March 9.See creative adaptations of vehicles of years past, from the solar-powered Nanook, to an amphicar that slides from land to sea and back again, to the stylish Bricklin SV-1 sportscar that inspired the famous DeLorean. Learn what a hearse, a tractor, and a sports car have in common. Let your imagination roam in the hands-on Tinker Garage.Race into RAM to check out DRIVE: Reimagining the Ride!

title: Edmonton Folk Music Festival
where_to_purchase_tickets: www.edmontonfolkfest.org for information www.frontgatetickets.com for tickets
short_description: Music Festival
additional_information: Line up announced and tickets available spring 2022.
notes_1: Beginning in 1980 with one staff and 300 volunteers, the Edmonton Folk Music Festival has grown and matured to become one of the leading folk festivals in the world. Now boasting a volunteer force of over 2700, the festival is a charitable not-for-profit society dedicated to bringing in the best of folk music from Edmonton, Canada, and around the world.
